article.headline: Wright St. 65, Wis.-Green Bay 54
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. (AP) -- DaShaun Wood had 23 points, six rebounds and five assists and Todd Brown added 17 points, as Wright State defeated Wisconsin-Green Bay 65-54 in a Horizon League game Monday night. The Raiders (15-8, 8-2) won for the sixth time in their last seven games and snapped Green Bays two-game winning streak. The Phoenix (12-10, 4-5) lost for only the second time at home all season, falling to 9-2 on their home floor. Green Bay was within 27-25 early in the second half, but the Phoenix never tied or took the lead. Wright State used a 11-2 run to take a 38-27 lead and Green Bay was never closer than seven the rest of the way. Wright State shot just 37 percent from the field, but the Raiders hit 19-of-22 from the free throw line, including 17-of-20 in the second half. Mike Schachtner led Green Bay with 14 points. Josh Lawrence added 13 points and six rebounds and Ryan Evanochko scored 12 points. But Schachtner and Evanochko, who average a combined 29.3 points per game for the Phoenix, finished a combined 7-of-24 from the floor. As a team, the Phoenix finished 16-of-45 (35.6 percent). Drew Burleson chipped in 10 points and eight rebounds for the Raiders, who swept the season series between the teams. Terry Evans finished with nine boards and five assists for Green Bay. Reigning Horizon League player of the week Troy Cotton was limited to seven points on 1-of-5 shooting for Green Bay.
